<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Core_Data">Core Data</span></h2>
<p>The core data is set to be used in the constructor, here:
</p>
<div dir="ltr" class="mw-geshi mw-code mw-content-ltr"><div class="cpp source-cpp"><pre class="de1">.<span class="me1">TreeItemsSource</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="sy3">&amp;</span>Directories <span class="br0">&#41;</span></pre></div></div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Summary">Summary</span></h2>
<p>Now you know the basics of using a tree view!
</p><p>You need
</p><p>1. your own custom data structure that is a node in the tree
</p><p>2. tree view .h
</p><p>3. tree view .cpp
</p><p>and that's all!
</p><p>Enjoy!
</p><p><a href="/User:Rama" title="User:Rama">Rama</a> (<a href="/User_talk:Rama" title="User talk:Rama">talk</a>)
</p>
